  array('id' => '190','region_id' => '8','title' => 'Shermain Jeremy','dob' => '1983-06-24','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Shermain Sunja Jeremy was born on the 24th of June, 1983 to the Hon. Longford Jeremy and Sonia Jeremy. She became a public figure when she won Miss Antigua Hal Jackson, and in 2002 when she won the local Miss Antigua Queen of carnival competition. She also won many regional competitions.[citation needed]

Jeremy went on to win the regional Jaycee\\\'s Caribbean Queen competition and the Miss PJD2 Caribbean 2003 in Dutch St. Maarten. In 2004 she represented her home country Antigua and Barbuda at the Miss World competition and was named the Most Talented Woman in the World.[citation needed] In 2005, Jeremy again represented her country at the Miss Universe competition, and though highly favored, she did not make it into the Top 15.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-12 00:04:44','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'shermain-jeremy'),
  array('id' => '191','region_id' => '10','title' => 'Gwyneth Paltrow','dob' => '1972-09-27','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Actress','description' => 'Paltrow was born in Los Angeles, California, and is the daughter of actress Blythe Danner and the late film producer/director Bruce Paltrow. Her father was Jewish and her mother is from a Christian background, and Paltrow was raised with &quot;both Jewish and Christian holidays&quot;.[10][11][12] Her father&#039;s Ashkenazi family immigrated from Belarus[13] and Poland,[14] while her mother&#039;s ancestry is Pennsylvania Dutch (German) and white Barbadian (English).','video' => '','image' => '1422406222wallpaper-di-gwyneth-paltrow-984772276.jpg','tags' => 'actress, producer, Entrepreneur, singer','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '4','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '2015-09-24','createdate' => '2014-06-12 00:04:44','postdate' => '2015-01-27 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => '','twittershortdesc' => '','slug' => 'gwyneth-paltrow'),
  array('id' => '192','region_id' => '10,2','title' => 'Jada Pinkett Smith','dob' => '1971-09-18','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Actress','description' => 'Born in Baltimore, Maryland, Jada Koren Pinkett was named after her mother&#039;s favorite soap-opera actress, Jada Rowland.[2] Pinkett-Smith is of African-American, West Indian, Creole, and Portuguese-Jewish ancestry.[3][4] Her parents are Adrienne Banfield-Jones, the head nurse of an inner-city clinic in Baltimore, and Robsol Pinkett Jr., who ran a construction company. Banfield-Jones became pregnant in high school; the couple married but divorced after several months.[5] Banfield-Jones raised Pinkett with the help of her mother, Marion Martin Banfield, a social worker.[6] Banfield noticed her granddaughter&#039;s passion for the performing arts and enrolled her in piano, tap dance, and ballet lessons.[7] She has a younger brother, actor/writer Caleeb Pinkett!','video' => '','image' => '1422395901NDgyMTU3NjExMjQoactress-jada-pinkett-smith-advocates-for-tougher-human-.jpg','tags' => 'actress, producer, Entrepreneur, singer','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '4','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '2015-05-08','createdate' => '2014-06-12 00:33:51','postdate' => '2015-03-03 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => 'Actress, Movie Star','twittershortdesc' => '','slug' => 'jada-pinkett-smith'),
  array('id' => '193','region_id' => '10','title' => 'Melyssa Ford','dob' => '1976-11-07','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Model','description' => 'Melyssa Savannah Ford (born November 7, 1976) is a Canadian model and actress.[3] She attended York University and studied in the field of forensic psychology.[4] Ford\\\'s father is Afro-Barbadian and her mother is Russian and Norwegian. She is often referred to as Jessica Rabbit, after the character from the animated film Who Framed Roger Rabbit whose voluptuous figure Ford\\\'s is said to resemble.[1][5]:3','video' => '','image' => 'peopleprofile-193.jpg','tags' => 'model, actress','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '3','admin_id' => '15','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '2015-05-30','createdate' => '2014-06-12 00:33:51','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => '','twittershortdesc' => '','slug' => 'melyssa-ford'),
  array('id' => '194','region_id' => '18','title' => 'Maurice DuBois','dob' => '1965-08-20','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'TV Star','description' => 'Maurice DuBois (born August 20, 1965) is an American television anchorman for WCBS-TV in New York City and the CBS network. DuBois was born on Long Island, New York, the son of immigrants to the U.S. from Dominica, an island nation in the Caribbean. He attended Port Jefferson High School,[1] and received a Bachelor of Science degree in journalism from Northwestern University in Evanston, Illinois.[2] While in college, he served as an intern at the Public OAffairs Office of the Brookhaven National Laboratory on Long Island in 1984 and 1985, where he wrote for the employee newspaper, the Brookhaven Bulletin.[3]','video' => '','image' => 'peopleprofile-194.jpg','tags' => 'anchorman','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '3','admin_id' => '15','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '2015-06-08','createdate' => '2014-06-12 00:33:51','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => '','twittershortdesc' => '','slug' => 'maurice-dubois'),
