  array('id' => '219','region_id' => '21','title' => 'Bruno Mars','dob' => '1985-10-08','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Singer','description' => 'Peter Gene Hernandez (born October 8, 1985), professionally known by his stage name: Bruno Mars, is an American singer-songwriter, record producer, voice actor, and choreographer. Born and raised in Honolulu, Hawaii, by a family of musicians, Mars began making music at a young age and performed in various musical venues in his hometown throughout his childhood. He graduated from high school and moved to Los Angeles to pursue a musical career. Mars produced songs for other artists, co-founding the production team','video' => '','image' => '1422402220Bruno-Mars-Wallpaper-HD-1200x900.jpg','tags' => 'Singer, songwriter, producer, song writer','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '4','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '2015-05-07','createdate' => '2014-06-12 21:55:13','postdate' => '2015-01-27 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => 'Recording Artist, Singer, Song writer ','twittershortdesc' => '','slug' => 'bruno-mars'),
  array('id' => '220','region_id' => '1','title' => 'Shama (Sham) Joseph','dob' => '1982-06-24','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Producer','description' => 'Haitian-American producer Shama (Sham) Joseph first landed on our radar with his production for Rihanna’s “Man Down.” The reggae-flavored hit (now officially a touchstone) brought RiRi back to her Caribbean roots but also grabbed our attention with the opening tag, “Sak Pase!”— “What’s happening” in Kreyòl. Building on the momentum of “Man Down,” Sham placed “Who Gon Stop Me” and “Made it in America,” two of the best tracks on Kanye West and Jay-Z’s blockbuster Watch the Throne album. Apparently, he was just getting warmed up, though, as a partial list of the artists he’s working with currently reads like a list of hip-hop, R&B and dancehall’s biggest hitmakers of the last 10 years: Sean Paul, T.I., Keyshia Cole, Usher, Ciara, Busta Rhymes, Chris Brown, Mavado. So whether you’ve got Haitian friends or not, get used to hearing “Sak Pase!” a whole hell of a lot. We recently spoke with the Fort Lauderdale, Florida native over the phone from his current homebase in Atlanta.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => 'producer, sham,','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '4','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 03:02:05','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'shama-sham-joseph'),
  array('id' => '221','region_id' => '2','title' => 'Junior Giscombe','dob' => '1957-06-06','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Singer','description' => 'For my money, British R&B singer Junior Giscombe‘s “Mama Used to Say” is one of the most crucial—and original—tributes to motherly wisdom, right up there with this and this. Not only is Junior of Jamaican heritage (he was born in London to Jamaican parents), but quite a few Caribbeans have put their own spin on “Mama” as well:','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => 'Singer, mama used to say, ','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '2015-04-21','createdate' => '2014-06-13 03:02:05','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'junior-giscombe'),
  array('id' => '222','region_id' => '2','title' => 'Claude Kelly','dob' => '0000-12-28','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Song writer','description' => 'Even at the tender age of 5, it was clear that Claude Kelly was destined for greatness.  His organ playing in church filled the pews, put money in his very small sized pockets and had all the church ladies on smash,  talking about what a prodigy this Jamerican youth from the East Village was…','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => 'song writer, musician,','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '4','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 03:02:05','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'claude-kelly'),
  array('id' => '223','region_id' => '2','title' => 'Nicola Vassel','dob' => '0000-00-00','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Flipped to the back of New York mag this morning to run through the crossword over my morning tea and what did I see but Jamaica’s favorite daughter and Large Up homegirl Nicola Vassel sashaying across Wooster street in a new Cole Haan ad. Not surprising maybe for a bonafide super-model, except that lately Nikki has been more at home on the other side of the eye-candy equation, making a name for herself as a curator with Deitch, the hottest gallery in SoH','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '4','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 03:02:05','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'nicola-vassel'),
  array('id' => '224','region_id' => '2','title' => 'Errol Kerr','dob' => '1986-04-12','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'For the first time, Jamaica will be represented at the Winter Olympics (which begin today in Vancouver) in a competition other than bobsledding. Errol Kerr, the son of an American mother and a Jamaican father who was born in Brooklyn and raised in California, is competing in skicross, a ski event held on a motocross-style obstacle course that is making its Olympic debut at this year’s Games. The decision to ski for JA instead of the U.S.A. is part tribute to Kerr’s father, who passed away 10 years ago, and part mission to enhance youth development in Jamaica. While he is the Jamaican Ski Team’s only rep at the Olympics this year, Kerr and his sponsors are engaging in a number of efforts to boost its profile, including a a contest to create a Jamaica Ski Team theme song. We caught up with Kerr earlier this week as he was making his final preparations before heading to Vancouver.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '4','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 03:02:05','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'errol-kerr'),
  array('id' => '225','region_id' => '17','title' => 'YUMILKA RUIZ LUACES','dob' => '1978-05-08','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Athletes','description' => 'Yumilka Ruíz born 8 May 1978 in Havana is a retired volleyball player from Cuba, who represented her native country in four consecutive Summer Olympics, starting in 1996. She twice won a gold medal with the national team in 1996 and 2000; she also claimed the bronze at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens, Greece.

