  array('id' => '340','region_id' => '4','title' => 'Jaslene Gonzalez','dob' => '1986-05-29','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Model','description' => 'Number 10 may have been the hardest to pick, since it is so naturally the one-to-watch spot and there are so many ones we’d like to watch. In the end we went with Jaslene Gonzalez of America’s Next Top Model fame. Although some of her growing pains and awkward first steps will be forever immortalized on youtube, the TV celebrity–and the contracts with Covergirl cosmetics and Seventeen magazine it’s engendered–have put her on the right path to stardom.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => 'Model, Fashion model, cover girl, ','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '2015-04-21','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:24:18','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'jaslene-gonzalez'),
  array('id' => '341','region_id' => '6','title' => 'Omahyra Mota','dob' => '1984-11-30','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Yet another native of Dominican Republic, Omahyra may be too edgy for some but she has made her punk chic look into a brand all it’s own and translated her modeling accolades (Victoria’s Secret, People’s Most Beautiful list, etc. etc) into a larger profile for herself, making her iconic and instantly recognizable presence felt in music videos and films like X-Men and After the Sunset. All of which begs the question: is DR shaping up to be for the 2010&#8242;s what Jamaica has been for some time now; a bottomless feeder school for global stardom. Omahyra was born on November 30, 1984 in Santo Domingo, Dominican Republic as Omahyra Mota Garcia. She is an actress, known for X-Men: The Last Stand (2006), After the Sunset (2004) and Happy End (2009)','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:24:18','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'omahyra-mota'),
  array('id' => '342','region_id' => '6','title' => 'Arlenis Sosa-Pena','dob' => '1989-05-07','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Model','description' => 'Another striking Dominicana, Arlenis is the current face of Lancome. In addition to appearing in various editions of Vogue and Harper’s and fashion shows for Victoria’s Secret and a host of the usual suspects, she made People mag’s “100 Most Beautiful People” list last year.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => 'Victoria’s Secret , model, Vogue, People magazine,','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:24:18','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'arlenis-sosa-pena'),
  array('id' => '343','region_id' => '6','title' => 'Sessilee Lopez','dob' => '1989-01-04','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Although relatively young in the fashion game, this beauty of Domican, Afro-American and Portuguese descent has already strutted her elegantly long frame and piercing eyes to the top, appearing on one of the four covers of Vogue Italia’s all-black everything issue–putting her on a par with Naomi and Liya Kebede. Although she has appeared in plenty of other mags and some major campaigns, her main claim to fame is still on the runway–where she has walked for the likes of Dolce & Gabbana, Fendi, Gaultier, Karl Lagerfeld, Marc Jacobs and Hermes','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:36:55','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'sessilee-lopez'),
  array('id' => '344','region_id' => '2','title' => 'Joey Bada$$','dob' => '1995-01-20','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Joey Bada$$ was the first of his immediate Jamaican family to be born in the US, so it was only a matter of time before he took it back to his Caribbean roots. The 18-year-old Brooklyn rapper, who has caught the hip-hop world’s attention with his wise-beyond-his-years lyricism and throwback ’90s style, headed to St. Lucia for his latest video, for the island-flavored track “My Yout.” Jo-Vaughn Virginie Scott, better known by his stage name Joey Badass, is an American hip hop recording artist from Bed Stuy, Brooklyn, New York City, New York','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:36:55','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'joey-bada'),
  array('id' => '345','region_id' => '4','title' => 'Carlos Beltran','dob' => '1977-04-24','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Athletes','description' => 'The most recognizable Boricua baseballer currently is veteran Mets centerfielder Carlos Beltran. baseball player','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => 'baseball player, NY Mets, centerfielder,','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:36:55','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'carlos-beltran'),
  array('id' => '346','region_id' => '17','title' => 'Kendrys Morales','dob' => '1983-06-20','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Barred from playing in his native Cuba after making contact with an agent, Morales defected to Florida on a raft in 2004. The first basemen was having a career-best year last season for the Los Angeles Angels, until September 10, when–after hitting what may be the most unfortunate game-winning grand slam of all time–he fractured his lower left leg while rounding home plate, and hasn’t played since. The lowly Angels eagerly anticipate his return.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:36:55','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'kendrys-morales'),
  array('id' => '347','region_id' => '24','title' => 'Mariano Rivera','dob' => '1969-11-29','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Every opposing team who plays in Yankee Stadium dreads the sound of Metallica’s “Enter Sandman”: that’s the music that comes on the PA when Mariano Rivera, the greatest and most consistent relief pitcher of all-time, is called in from the bullpen. Rivera’s reputation as an unflappable stopper has even even made him a reference point in hip-hop lyrics. See Jay-Z’s “More than a relief pitcher, I’m the closer/The Mariano of the Marriott” line from Young Jeezy’s “Go Crazy.”','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:36:55','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'mariano-rivera'),
  array('id' => '348','region_id' => '6','title' => 'Jose Bautista','dob' => '1980-10-19','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Little known before last season, Toronto Blue Jays right fielder Bautista led the majors in 2010 with a team-record 54 home runs. He has continued his torrid hitting in 2011, becoming the first player in the majors to reach 20 home runs, and earning American League Player of the Month honors for both April and May. (In fact, he’s won those honors for four of the last five months, dating back to July of last year.) Deservedly, he led all players in voting for today’s All-Star game.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:36:55','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'jose-bautista'),
  array('id' => '349','region_id' => '6','title' => 'Jose Reyes','dob' => '1983-06-11','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Athletes','description' => 'Widely considered the most exciting player in baseball on account of his youthful enthusiasm and blazing-fast speed, Reyes was having the best season of his career this year after spending much of the past few years on the sidelines due to injuries. He’s hurt once again and likely to leave New York as a free agent after the season, but at least us long-suffering Mets supporters have his reggaeton career to look forward to.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => 'baseball, mets, ','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '2015-04-21','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:36:55','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'jose-reyes'),
  array('id' => '350','region_id' => '6','title' => 'Robinson Cano','dob' => '1982-10-22','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Though infinitely less recognizable than his neighbors in the Yankee infield, A-Rod and Derek Jeter, Robinson Cano is unquestionably the best second baseman in the Majors. To top it off, he won yesterday’s Home Run Derby, a feat pretty much unheard of for a middle infielder.Alex Rodriguez','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:36:55','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'robinson-cano'),
  array('id' => '351','region_id' => '6','title' => 'Alex Rodriguez (A-Rod)','dob' => '1977-07-27','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Athletes','description' => 'Born in Washington Heights and raised primarily in Miami, A-Rod isn’t a product of the DR baseball system like the other Dominicans on this list but he did live there briefly as a kid. And though his sometimes off-putting personality, headline-grabbing relationships (with Madonna, Cameron Diaz and about a dozen other celebs whose names we can’t recall) and the uncanny numbers he put up in Texas and Seattle can obscure his achievements, Rodriguez has been everything he was supposed to be since signing with the Yankees in the biggest free-agent deal of all time.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => 'baseball player, athlete, baseball, Yankees','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:36:55','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'alex-rodriguez-a-rod'),
  array('id' => '352','region_id' => '6','title' => 'Albert Pujols','dob' => '1980-01-16','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Athletes','description' => 'Having missed most of this season with a wrist injury, the Cardinals’ big-swinging first baseman won’t play in today’s All-Star Game, but he has been the most dominant offensive player in the Major Leagues for the last half-decade or more.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => 'baseball, athletes,','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:36:55','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'albert-pujols'),
  array('id' => '353','region_id' => '2','title' => 'Master T','dob' => '0000-00-00','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'A generation of Canadian ’80s babies grew up watching Xtendamix on MuchMusic every Saturday afternoon. Tony “Master T” Young came from Jamaica to Toronto via Leeds, and he showcased low-budget dancehall videos alongside the finest in hip hop and R&B. But what really set him apart was his friendly demeanor, synthesizer co-host Roxy, and penchant for sporadically hosting the show in character as his Scottish cousin McT or Santa T. A true original, T introduced the fresh, forward-thinking side of West Indian culture to young Canadians.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:44:59','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'master-t'),
  array('id' => '354','region_id' => '1','title' => 'Georges Laraque','dob' => '1976-12-07','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'There are black people in the NHL! And not all of them play for Atlanta (well, Winnipeg). Born in Montréal to Haitian parents, 6’4”-, 250-pound Georges Laraque was a notorious enforcer during his years in the league. But he earned the respect of his peers as a clean fighter on the ice and a gentle giant off of it. Since retiring in 2010, he’s entered politics and business, becoming deputy leader of the Green Party and investing in a chain of vegan restaurants. His short-lived mixed martial arts career was less successful','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:44:59','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'georges-laraque'),
  array('id' => '355','region_id' => '5','title' => 'Little X (AKA \\"Director X\\")','dob' => '1975-10-31','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'This half-Trini hails from Brampton–sort of a suburban Crown Heights, just outside of Toronto–and started his career as a teenage intern at MuchMusic, our version of MTV. He soon moved on to work for Hype Williams, learning enough to earn his own gigs and going on to direct classics like Sean Paul’s crossover trinity of “Gimme the Light,” “Get Busy” and “Temperature,” as well as big American hits like Usher’s “Yeah” and Kanye’s “The New Workout Plan.” We’ll always remember him for his role as visual consultant on the stylistically stunning Belly. Did he put those rooster feathers on Sosa’s head?t','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:44:59','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'little-x-aka-director-x'),
  array('id' => '356','region_id' => '2','title' => 'Kardinal Offishall','dob' => '1976-05-12','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Kardi started his rap career as ”Kool Aid” but switched his name up as a teen, inspired by iron-fisted 17th-century French politician Cardinal Richelieu. Since the son of Jamaican immigrants first burst out of T-O in the late 90s, he’s appeared on everything from the “selector remix” of Clipse’s “Grindin’” to a Paragons/Blondie cover. But he earned his place in history with the phenomenal “Ol’ Time Killin’,” which fuses bare chat about sound bwoy murder with Little X visuals featuring some of the most vibrant Caribbean coloration ever to grace the small screen.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:44:59','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'kardinal-offishall'),
  array('id' => '357','region_id' => '22','title' => 'Hype Williams','dob' => '0000-00-00','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Video director, Williams has created a number of music videos for many artists, including 2Pac (\\"California Love\\"), The Notorious B.I.G. (\\"Warning\\") and (\\"One More Chance\\"), Craig Mack (\\"Flava in Ya Ear\\" (Remix)), LL Cool J (\\"Doin\\\' It\\"), Nas (\\"If I Ruled the World (Imagine That)\\", \\"Street Dreams\\", \\"Hate Me Now\\"), Missy Elliott (\\"The Rain (Supa Dupa Fly))\\", \\"She\\\'s a Bitch\\"), Busta Rhymes (\\"Put Your Hands Where My Eyes Could See\\"), TLC (\\"No Scrubs\\"), Kelis (\\"Caught Out There\\"), Jay-Z (\\"Big Pimpin\\\'\\"), Kanye West (\\"Gold Digger\\", \\"Heartless\\",[1] \\"All of the Lights\\", \\"Diamonds from Sierra Leone\\"), Aaliyah (\\"Rock the Boat\\"), Christina Aguilera (\\"Not Myself Tonight\\"), Coldplay (\\"Viva la vida\\"), Ne-Yo (\\"So Sick\\"), Hoobastank (\\"If I Were You\\"), Left Eye (The Block Party), t.A.T.u. (\\"Gomenasai\\"), Ke$ha (\\"We R Who We R\\"), Meek Mill (\\"Levels\\"), Nicki Minaj (\\"Massive Attack\\" \\"Va Va Voom\\") and \\"Stupid Hoe\\", Jack White (\\"Freedom at 21\\") and Beyoncé (\\"Drunk in Love\\").','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:44:59','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'hype-williams'),
  array('id' => '358','region_id' => '2','title' => 'Michael Lee-Chin','dob' => '1951-01-03','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'The black Warren Buffett is a Chinese Jamaican from Port Antonio who moved to Canada to attend McMaster University. After school, he took advantage of the late-80s mutual funds explosion to cultivate a financial services empire with fingers in investment planning, securities and insurance. After working his way onto the Forbes Billionaires list, Lee-Chin cashed out in 2009 and shifted his wealth to extensive holdings across the Caribbean in sectors like banking,
telecommunications and Reggae Beach. Lee-Chin is well-known in Canada for his numerous philanthropic efforts, including his questionable taste in architecture.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:44:59','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'michael-lee-chin'),
  array('id' => '359','region_id' => '1','title' => 'The Right Honourable Michaëlle Jean','dob' => '1957-09-06','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Entrepreneur','description' => 'In 2005, Jean was appointed Governor-General–the Queen’s representative in Canada and our country’s ceremonial head of state. Jean was born in Haiti and moved to Montréal as a teenager, where her academic career focused on comparative literature and languages (she speaks five). After working her way up to national prominence as a journalist, she accepted the five-year term and focused her efforts on youth issues and support for the armed forces. Perhaps her best-known act as “G-G” was responding to Europe’s ban on seal meat by jetting up north to eat raw seal heart in solidarity with the Inuit hunters. Since leaving office in 2010, Jean has become special envoy to Haiti for the UN.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => 'Governor General the Queen’s, Canada, ceremonial head of state, Montréal, journalist, UN,','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:44:59','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'the-right-honourable-michalle-jean'),
  array('id' => '360','region_id' => '2','title' => 'Malcolm Gladwell','dob' => '1963-09-03','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'This half-Jamaican journalist is a gifted storyteller, famous for writing long-form New Yorker articles that make you feel smarter afterwards and for turning the best ones into best-sellers like Blink, Outliers and The Tipping Point. Gladwell’s West Indian heritage doesn’t often feature in his work, but he touches on it in this piece on the relationship between sporting excellence and race, and in this radio interview on the same topic.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:44:59','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'malcolm-gladwell'),
  array('id' => '361','region_id' => '31','title' => 'Thierry Henry','dob' => '1977-08-17','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Athletes','description' => '','video' => '','image' => 'peopleprofile-361.jpg','tags' => 'football, soccer, world cup,','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '3','admin_id' => '15','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '2015-06-10','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:59:06','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => '','twittershortdesc' => '','slug' => 'thierry-henry'),
  array('id' => '362','region_id' => '10','title' => 'Ashley Cole','dob' => '1980-12-20','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Athletes','description' => 'A staple presence in the British tabloids, Cole recently led Chelsea to the Premier League title after missing most of the season to injury. Most of the the headlines he’s generated lately have been about his impending divorce from singer/X Factor judge Cheryl Cole, though.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => 'football, soccer, chelsea,','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:59:06','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'ashley-cole'),
  array('id' => '363','region_id' => '31','title' => 'Eric Abidal','dob' => '1979-09-11','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Born in Lyon to parents from Martinique, Thierry Henry’s Barcelona F.C. teammate is part of a long line of Antillean defenders to play prominent roles on France’s national team.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:59:06','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'eric-abidal'),
  array('id' => '364','region_id' => '1','title' => 'Jozy Altidore','dob' => '1989-11-06','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Born in New Jersey to Haitian parents, the former New York Red Bulls and current Villareal C.F. striker has been one of the U.S. team’s most hyped players coming into the World Cup, and he lived up to it in Saturday’s game versus the U.K., coming thisclose to netting the game-winning goal in the 64th minute. Soca Warriors fans will remember Altidore from last April’s World Cup qualifier when he single-handedly outscored the T&T squad 3-0.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:59:06','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'jozy-altidore'),
  array('id' => '365','region_id' => '26','title' => 'Jermain Defoe','dob' => '1982-10-07','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Defoe, whose mother comes from St. Lucia, recently scored five goals in a game on his way to becoming one of the Premier League’s top scorers in 2009/10. The Tottenham striker is expected to be one of the key offensive weapons for an English team with immense pressure on its shoulders.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:59:06','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'jermain-defoe'),
  array('id' => '366','region_id' => '5','title' => 'Stern John','dob' => '1976-10-30','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Athletes','description' => 'John, currently playing for Crystal Palace in the Premier League, was the most pivotal player in the Soca Warriors 2006 World Cup run. He’s also T&T’s all-time leading scorer. Stern John CM is a Trinidadian football player who recently came out of retirement to play for WASA FC.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => 'Crystal Palace in the Premier League, Soca Warriors, football, soccer,','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-13 09:59:06','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'stern-john'),
