  array('id' => '552','region_id' => '5','title' => 'ESAU MEILING','dob' => '0000-00-00','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'ESAU MEILING is a Trinidadian-born designer with a knack for creating truly special designs. Her attention to detail is legendary and she is known to create beautiful garments from linen and other natural fabrics. And though her designs are in no way laughable, she believes \\&quot;the woman who wears a Meiling design should have wit, humour and an ability to laugh at herself.\\&quot; Today, the graduate of the Lucie Clayton School of Design in London, England, is regarded as one of the Caribbean\\\'s best designers.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-18 08:48:58','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'esau-meiling'),
  array('id' => '553','region_id' => '1','title' => 'Charles Corvsky Dieujuste','dob' => '0000-00-00','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Fashion Designer','description' => 'At the early age of nine, Charles Corvsky Dieujuste was inspired to become a fashion designer while growing up in the great island of Haiti. While inheriting his rich culture, and being surrounded by plush green mountains and colorful flowers, this backdrop stimulated his mind to design feminine aesthetic, romanticism and classical elegant clothing. Dieujuste is now ready to take over the fashion world with his newest Fall 2013 Collection.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => 'fashion, designer,','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-18 08:48:58','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'charles-corvsky-dieujuste'),
  array('id' => '554','region_id' => '1,4','title' => 'Jean-Michel Basquiat','dob' => '1960-12-22','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Jean-Michel Basquiat, born in Brooklyn, New York, was the second of four children of Matilda Andrades (July 28, 1934 – November 17, 2008)[4] and Gerard Basquiat (born 1930 - died July 7, 2013[5]).[6] He had two younger sisters: Lisane, born in 1964, and Jeanine, born in 1967.[4]

His father, Gerard Basquiat, was born in Port-au-Prince, Haiti, and his mother, Matilde Basquiat, of Afro-Puerto Rican descent, was born in Brooklyn, New York. Matilde instilled a love for art in her young son by taking him to art museums in Manhattan and enrolling him as a junior member of the Brooklyn Museum of Art.[6][7] Basquiat was a precocious child who learned how to read and write by age four and was a gifted artist. His teachers noticed his artistic abilities, and his mother encouraged her son\\\'s artistic talent. By the age of 11, Basquiat could fluently speak, read and write French, Spanish and English.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-18 08:48:58','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'jean-michel-basquiat'),
  array('id' => '555','region_id' => '31','title' => 'Ronny Turiaf','dob' => '1983-01-13','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Known for his defensive play, animated bench presence and long cornrows, the Martinique-born Turiaf attended high school in France before playing at Gonzaga University and for the Lakers, Warriors and Knicks. A fan favorite in every city he’s played, Turiaf was traded to the Washington Wizards last week. Ronny Turiaf is a French professional basketball player who currently plays for the Minnesota Timberwolves of the National Basketball Association. Turiaf has been a member of the French national basketball team.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => '','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2014-06-18 09:03:38','postdate' => '0000-00-00 00:00:00','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'ronny-turiaf'),
