  array('id' => '654','region_id' => '2','title' => 'Fefe Dobson','dob' => '1985-02-28','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Others','description' => 'Dobson\\\'s mother is of English, Aboriginal, and French ancestry and her father is of Jamaican heritage. Felicia Lily \\&quot;Fefe\\&quot; Dobson (born February 28, 1985) is a Canadian songwriter and recording artist. Born in Toronto, Canada, her career began when Jive Records attempted to develop her as a popular musician which Dobson refused, Dobson then sang for Island/Def Jam in which the executives contracted her.

