  array('id' => '992','region_id' => '9','title' => 'T-Pain','dob' => '1985-09-30','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Singer','description' => 'Faheem Rashad Najm better known by his stage name T-Pain, is an American singer, songwriter, rapper, record producer, and actor. His debut album, Rappa Ternt Sanga, was released in 2005. In 2007, T-Pain released his second studio album Epiphany, which reached number one on the Billboard 200. His third studio album, Thr33 Ringz, was released in 2008. T-Pain has earned two Grammy Awards alongside artists Kanye West and Jamie Foxx.','video' => '','image' => 'peopleprofile-992.jpg','tags' => 'Singer,Rapper, Auto Tune, ','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2015-04-13 04:05:09','postdate' => '2015-04-13 04:05:09','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 't-pain'),
  array('id' => '1003','region_id' => '2','title' => 'Barrington Levy','dob' => '1964-04-30','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Singer','description' => 'Levy was born in Clarendon, Jamaica. He formed a band called the Mighty Multitude, with his cousin, Everton Dacres; the pair released \\"My Black Girl\\" in 1977.[1][2] Levy established his solo career the next year with \\"A Long Time Since We Don\\\'t Have No Love\\";[2] though the single was a failure, the fourteen-year-old was a popular performer at Jamaican dancehalls.[3] In an August 2014 interview with Midnight Raver, record producer Delroy Wright revealed that it was his brother Hyman Wright who first met Barrington Levy in the mid-1970s through Wade \\"Trinity\\" Brammer. According to Delroy Wright, Hyman Wright recorded a host of tracks with Barrington Levy prior to introducing him to Henry \\"Junjo\\" Lawes. These tracks would eventually appear on the album Bounty Hunter, which was released on the Jah Life record label.','video' => '','image' => 'peopleprofile-1003.com-506174','tags' => 'singer, dancehall, reggae, ','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '2015-04-14','createdate' => '2015-04-14 11:37:04','postdate' => '2015-04-14 11:37:04','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'barrington-levy'),
