  array('id' => '1012','region_id' => '26','title' => 'Derek Alton Walcott','dob' => '1930-01-23','kind' => 'People profile','category' => 'Poet','description' => 'Derek Alton Walcott, OBE OCC (born 23 January 1930) is a Saint Lucian poet and playwright. He received the 1992 Nobel Prize in Literature.[1] He is currently Professor of Poetry at the University of Essex. His works include the Homeric epic poem Omeros (1990), which many critics view \\"as Walcott\\\'s major achievement.\\"[2][3] In addition to having won the Nobel, Walcott has won many literary awards over the course of his career, including an Obie Award in 1971 for his play Dream on Monkey Mountain, a MacArthur Foundation \\"genius\\" award, a Royal Society of Literature Award, the Queen\\\'s Medal for Poetry, the inaugural OCM Bocas Prize for Caribbean Literature[4] and the 2011 T. S. Eliot Prize for his book of poetry White Egrets.[5] Following his receiving the T. S. Eliot Prize in 2011, Walcott is recognized as one of the principal contributors to poetry in the early 21st century.','video' => '','image' => '','tags' => 'poet, playwright,','facebook' => '','twitter' => '','facebookfanpage' => '','twitterfanpage' => '','instagram' => '','status' => '1','admin_id' => '1','conform' => '0','modifydate' => '0000-00-00','createdate' => '2015-04-15 01:16:33','postdate' => '2015-04-15 01:16:33','rejectreason' => '','shortdesc' => NULL,'twittershortdesc' => NULL,'slug' => 'derek-alton-walcott'),
